Hello,

I use `TexturePacker2` to pack textures into one atlas. 

It supports `stripWhitespaceX` and `stripWhitespaceY` options to strip whitespace at borders of every image. But i've noticed that if I render `TextureRegion`'s with these options  the regions size is corrupted. 

There is an example what I am talking about: 
![atlasregiondrawable](https://f.cloud.github.com/assets/1666014/1863407/2b270e56-77e2-11e3-854e-96aaa870f05c.png)
Original image (a), packed (b) and currupted render (c)

So, i decided to [dig deeper](https://github.com/libgdx/libgdx/wiki/Texture-packer#settings), and I've noticed that there are no support for drawing `Atlas$AtlasRegion`'s additinal data for that (`OffsetX`, `OffsetY`, `OriginalWidth` etc) correctly (if I am right).

So, I wrote it by myself, and glad to contribute it to Community, if it is possible.

``` java
package com.badlogic.gdx.scenes.scene2d.utils;


import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.SpriteBatch;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.TextureAtlas;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.TextureRegion;
import com.badlogic.gdx.scenes.scene2d.utils.BaseDrawable;

public class AtlasRegionDrawable extends BaseDrawable
{
    private TextureAtlas.AtlasRegion region;
    private float coefWidth;
    private float coefHeight;
    private float coefX;
    private float coefY;

    public AtlasRegionDrawable () {
    }

    public AtlasRegionDrawable (TextureAtlas.AtlasRegion region) {
        setRegion(region);
    }

    public AtlasRegionDrawable (AtlasRegionDrawable drawable) {
        super(drawable);
        setRegion(drawable.region);
    }

    @Override
    public void draw (SpriteBatch batch, float x, float y, float width, float height) {
        batch.draw(region,
                x + coefX * (width - width * coefWidth),
                y + coefY * (height - height * coefHeight),
                width * coefWidth,
                height * coefHeight);
    }

    public void draw (SpriteBatch batch, float x, float y,
        float originX, float originY, float width, float height,
        float scaleX, float scaleY, float rotation) {

        batch.draw(region,
                x + coefX * (width - width * coefWidth),
                y + coefY * (height - height * coefHeight),

                originX - coefX * (width - width * coefWidth),
                originY - coefY * (height - height * coefHeight),

                width * coefWidth,
                height * coefHeight,
                scaleX, scaleY, rotation);
    }

    public void setRegion (TextureAtlas.AtlasRegion region) {

        this.region = region;

        if (region.originalWidth == region.packedWidth && region.originalHeight == region.packedHeight)
        {
            this.coefX = 0;
            this.coefY = 0;
            this.coefWidth = 1;
            this.coefHeight = 1;
        }
        else
        {
            this.coefWidth = (float)region.packedWidth / (float)region.originalWidth;
            this.coefHeight = (float)region.packedHeight / (float)region.originalHeight;
            this.coefX = region.offsetX / (float)(region.originalWidth - region.packedWidth);
            this.coefY = region.offsetY / (float)(region.originalHeight - region.packedHeight);
        }

        setMinWidth(region.originalWidth);
        setMinHeight(region.originalHeight);
    }

    public TextureRegion getRegion () {
        return region;
    }
}
```

I've used it in `Image` for the first time, and i've noticed that `Image` dont supports `Atlas$AtlasRegion` too. There is modification for it (i've created inherited class `AtlasImage`, but this code could be easly inserted into original `Image`) that renders `AtlasRegionDrawable` correctly:

``` java
    @Override
    public void draw(SpriteBatch batch, float parentAlpha)
    {
        validate();

        Color color = getColor();
        batch.setColor(color.r, color.g, color.b, color.a * parentAlpha);

        Drawable drawable = getDrawable();
        if (drawable != null) {
            if (drawable instanceof AtlasRegionDrawable) {
                AtlasRegionDrawable region = (AtlasRegionDrawable)drawable;

                float rotation = getRotation();
                if (getScaleX() == 1 && getScaleY() == 1 && rotation == 0)
                {
                    region.draw(batch,
                            getX() + getImageX(), getY() + getImageY(),
                            getImageWidth(), getImageHeight());

                    return;
                }
                else
                {
                    region.draw(batch,
                            getX() + getImageX(), getY() + getImageY(),
                            getOriginX() - getImageX(), getOriginY() - getImageY(),
                            getImageWidth(), getImageHeight(),
                            getScaleX(), getScaleY(), rotation);

                    return;
                }
            }
        }

        super.draw(batch, parentAlpha);
    }
```

(`draw` method only)

